Open the wfn.in file and inspect the k-points which are used here. These are the same ones as in the patch we generated in the previous step.

You can run the nscf calculation as per usual. 

Next, inspect the wfn.pp.in file. Which values are used for the k-grid dimensions? Why? Go ahead and run pw2bgw.x as usual with this input.

We are now ready to perform a BSE calculation on a patch.
